description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity to join our ESP team as a flexible member of our therapy workforce.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you an expert musculoskeletal physiotherapist looking for an flexible new challenge? An opportunity has arisen for an experienced musculoskeletal physiotherapist to join the Physiotherapy Department to work at an Extended Scope of Practice (ESP) level. The role wll involve working in our out-patient MSK service, Orthopaedic Surgery clinics and first contact practitioner clinics in primary care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, motivated and highly experienced and competent MSK Physiotherapist with a commitment to patient focused care, maintaining their CPD / specialist skills and who can work flexibly which may include evenings and weekends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will join an established team of ESP Physiotherapists, which provides input into Orthopaedic, Sports &amp; Exercise Medicine, and FCP clinics. You will be working as part of a multi-disciplinary team, including ESP’s, Advanced Nurse Practitioners, and medical colleagues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we can offer a dynamic and friendly working environment with support from an established team of advanced grade practitioners. There is a structured appraisal system and in-service training programme and opportunities for your continuing personal and professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
